Author: Jerry138889
Title: [ANN][TOKEN] RxEAL - THE LATEST WAY TO PROFIT FROM RENTAL MARKETS
Body: Forgive me if I am misunderstanding the project, but from what I read on the website, you need to have either ETH or DAI to invest into this escrow type facility. Don't you think that this is a huge barrier to entry for 99% of renters and landlords who have no idea about crypto?  What should be happening is that people can fund the escrow with their local currency and then you work out the escrow from there. I'm talking about usability and if you think people are genuinely going to go to Coinbase/equivalent, buy $¬£‚Ç¨1000 worth of eth and stick it in this, then you are crazy. It's not going to happen. People need to feel like they're not using crypto at all.  From their point of view, it needs to be that they send money from their bank account or paypal or venmo or whatever to your contract, you work out how to place that into escrow and then use your token to work out the arbitration/payment etc.  Am I misunderstanding how your business model works? I welcome a rebuttal.

Author: dpositMaster
Title: [ANN][TOKEN] RxEAL - THE LATEST WAY TO PROFIT FROM RENTAL MARKETS
Body: Again, absolutely different concept. We are the focused on rental security deposits on various markets, not only real estate, for instance car rental is one of the business verticals with extremely large market size. We are not aiming to replace whole renting process, we are focusing on the part that requires a blockchain solution to eliminate the trust issue of other party holding/returning your deposits.  There are platforms already that work pretty well for property listings without blockchain and there are cryptocurrencies for payments without the need for token. While our service can act as an additional layer for already functioning platforms and existing internal solutions for large rental companies as well. One of the biggest differences is that we are cooperating and not disrupting like most others tend to do. If we would be stealing the whole process of let‚Äôs say Airbnb, guess who has more resources and would easily outperform, this is why we are focusing on working together, not against.

Author: dpositMaster
Title: [ANN][TOKEN] RxEAL - THE LATEST WAY TO PROFIT FROM RENTAL MARKETS
Body: This is a good question. The answer is that we do not have access to the funds, the funds are stored inside a mutual contract on the blockchain that belongs only to both lessor and lessee - this is why it is called a trustless storage, as you do not have to trust your money to a third party. We are providing an interface to create and interact with these trustless contracts with no technical knowledge.  Moreover, storing deposit in Ethers can prove to be a very valuable investment over time and it can be worth much more than when security deposit was made. If you do not want to take the risk of value change, our contracts will also work with Dai stable coin developed by Maker.
